description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wye Valley NHS Trust -&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fundraising Manager - Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed term or Secondment Opportunity for 6 months with possibility of extension &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a highly motivated, engaging and enthusiastic Fundraising Manager who is looking to take the next step in your career? If so, why not join Wye Valley NHS Trust and make a difference to people’s lives in Herefordshire.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is a fixed term or secondment opportunity for 6 months with a possibility of extension and could be part time or full time. It is a key role within the Trust and the current post holder is on maternity leave. The successful candidate will lead on developing and implementing the Trust’s fundraising strategy. You will be responsible for developing and implementing a successful programme of fundraising from the corporate and business sector, meeting agreed financial income and expenditure budgets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will maximise donations to the Trust’s existing range of funds as well as raising income for specific projects. Build and maintain good relationships with existing networks and partnerships and establish new ones in order to maximise fundraising activity. Be responsible for achieving agreed targets to generate an agreed income for the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will ensure at all times that effective communications and good working relationships are maintained with all internal and external stakeholders including private and corporate donors, volunteers, charitable organisations, partners and Trust staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for producing and delivering high quality, creative, persuasive and accurate pitches and proposals, ensuring a tailored approach at all times, and developing and writing funding proposals, corporate applications and reports.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have creative ideas of how to generate income from the corporate and business community within Herefordshire. You will have demonstrable experience working in fundraising, either in the charity or corporate sector, ideally having business development or account management experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a pro-active individual with excellent written, verbal and networking skills and the ability to build strong relationships, both internal and external and at a range of levels. You will be a confident speaker, capable of delivering inspiring pitches and influencing potential and existing supporters. You will be highly organised with the ability to prioritise and manage your workload and multi-task.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will require a full clean driving licence and have the use of a vehicle for business purposes associated with this role, as you may be required to travel across Herefordshire. Flexibility over hours worked is important for the role, which will include occasional evening and weekend work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion about this opportunity, please contact :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alan Dawson, Director of Strategy &amp; Planning email: alan.dawson@wvt.nhs.uk or call 01432 364000&lt;/p&gt;
